project_descr: The use of innovations in information and communication technologies for development planning and policymaking in the area of trade and competitiveness, frontline service delivery, government information management and social protection.

outputs.output_descr: Turning ideas on how information required for decision-making can be collected, processed, presented and shared into practical software applications that government institutions and partner programmes can then adopt and build into their processes.

Turning ideas on how information required for decision-making can be collected, processed, presented and shared into practical software applications that government institutions and partner programmes can then adopt and build into their processes.

Successful deployment of new information technology improves productivity and increases trade competitiveness and ultimately the goal of this project is to increase productivity and improve the competitiveness of poor people.
